title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.2 EARLY CHILDHOOD EDUCATION

description.narrative: Output 2 (Early childhood education): National and subnational governments and partners have enhanced capacity and mechanisms to implement effective strategies and programmes that improve access to and quality of early childhood education., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: An increasing proportion of girls and boys, across the life cycle, especially the most disadvantaged, are learning in quality, safe and inclusive environments.

title.narrative: Output 2 (Early childhood education): National and subnational governments and partners have enhanced capacity and mechanisms toimplement effective strategies and programmes that improve access to and quality of early childhood education.

description.narrative: Commitment from the national and subnational governments for the Holistic and Integrative Early Childhood Development (HI-ECD) programme is strengthening. The launch of the HI-ECD National Action Plan for the period 2020–2024, supported by UNICEF, contributed to improvements in both the regulation and funding of HI-ECD implementation at subnational levels. Work relating to early childhood education, parenting and SDG monitoring has also shown positive progress, particularly concerning the effective transition from pre-primary to primary education, community-based parenting and the adaptation of the Early Child Development Index (ECDI2030) instrument to measure child development outcomes in the Indonesian context. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:03/02/2022
